Use the standard library
This is how to histogram of test:
   Remember that counts is {}
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this test's length times:
      Remember that c is item i in test
      When c is in counts, then:
         Increase item c in counts
      But, if not:
         Remember that item c in counts is 1
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that keys is unique_chars of test
   Remember that j is 0
   Do this keys's length times:
      Remember that k is item j in keys
      Add result to [k, item k in counts]
      Increase j
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> histogram of ""
[]